          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "New York’s pension fund, which covers 1.1 million members, retirees and beneficiaries, workers, has become a huge source of dark money for Wall Street. The fund shifted from investing 14 percent of its portfolio in alternative investments in 2004 to 25 percent today, resulting in $69 billion in pension fund resources allocated to alternative investment firms.",
